Kaisann, how did I disregard anything you said?  You asked how I had a problem with mana regen and I explained why mana regen is incredibly situational, to demonstrate that in SOME situations mana regen can be critical.  I didn't even bother to go into the fact that if I am not using my mana to heal the wizard I can do many other things...  mark of kings, mark of righteousness, pet, I can yaulp/melee with a proc hammer (which reduces mana regen but increases damage a LOT), I can nuke, it gives me more mana to buff my groupmates without making them wait for me to get a safe margin again after casting said buffs, etc...  I am not going to waste my time listing everything.<br>
<br>
You also claim that you have no problems keeping people such as overnuking wizards alive with just a celestial healing...  sure that may work in valor or BoT or something, but if you are xping in earth, trash mobs hit for 700s VERY QUICKLY, have nasty procs, etc...  so you're telling me that you can keep a wizard alive using just a 300hp/tick elixir when that person is taking ~700 DPS?  Supernal Elixir at 500/tick won't even keep up with that, not to mention that by the time you start casting that wonderful 3-4 second casting time spell, the wizard has already incurred one round of melee.  So 3 seconds later when the elixir lands the wizard is down about 3000 hps or more of their 4-5000 hp, putting them in or near low life frenzy aggro range, at which point they get pasted.<br>
