<br>
The entire point is:  Wizards had two claims to fame. Not necessarily listed in any order: 1) Ports (which for convenience sake got us invited to groups, to a lesser degree but still)<br>
<br>
and 2) Massive damage output.<br>
<br>
The problem?  PoP scratch idea number one..the albeit small but ever present &quot;Wizzies can port&quot; factor is negated.<br>
<br>
The BIG problem?  Wizards have but on major usage.  Damage! Damage! Damage!  Hmm We cannot but buff (thank goodness!), we cannot heal (That belongs to the other classes), we cannot pull (in most cases, besides, Rangers need something to die for /snicker), nor can we CR very effectively.  But we can dish out the punishment!  Er we used to be the best at it. <br>
<br>
Thing is now, a Ranger with AM3 can really dish it out too as well as host of other useful skills.  Magician, although they whine and moan (like the rest of us) they are heavy damage dealers.  They can CoH, debuff and the pet is great dps.  They also have some very nice rain spells and some good DD's (slower casting and more mana but still they have the nice pets let's not forget..WHICH they can also heal!).  The Rogue, ever hear a Rogue say, &quot;Med break? OOM!&quot;  Nope and that is not a problem with the Ranger either.  If the Mage is OOM, no biggie, his/her pet just keep embarassing the groups tank.  All three can do more than the Wizard and all three can rival or come darn close to our damage output with little or no OOM.<br>
<br>
This is why Wizards cannot get groups.  The current game conditions and situation literally make the Wizard not needed and less than desirable until we make 60 plus and obtain certain AA abilities.<br>
<br>
Sad but true.  <br>
<br>
