Sorry, we were talking about wizards overnuking and having to be healed (among other things) and you made a statement that you 'never had to mem SR at all and was often able to keep people alive using just celestial elixir' so I took that to mean wizards some of the time too.  Arbitration is arguably the best cleric xp group ability in the game, I love it to death (which it usually saves me from) and yeah it is great to stack an elixir on a wizard and arbitrate them back into a safe HP range...  but arb only refreshes every 3 minutes and if the wizard overaggros again in that time you may not be fast enough...  besides, why should I have to waste my arb healing a wizard that shouldn't be getting owned in the first place?  If a lazy wizard sucks up my arbitration, I can't use it next time a mob adds and pastes the chanter unexpectedly or slow resists or any of the other myriad situations where arb is useful.  Nope.  It's gone, because some wizard who *COULD* have kept from getting aggro, didn't care enough not to.  This leaves supernal light as your only remaining targetable fast heal... which isn't an ideal choice, it is twice as slow casting as supernal remedy, less mana efficient, generates more aggro, and usually heals more damage than the wizard has taken.<br>
