<br>
DPM = Damage Per Mana<br>
<br>
Strike of Solusek: 2740 dmg for 640 mana = 4.28 DPM<br>
Tears of Marr: 850x3=2550 dmg for 425mana = 6 DPM<br>
Tears of Marr: 850x2=1700 dmg for 425 mana = 4 DPM<br>
Tears of Arylixir: 645x3=1935dmg for 420mana = 4.61 DPM<br>
Draught of Ro, E'ci, etc: 950 dmg for 255 mana= 3.72 DPM<br>
<br>
Tears of Marr stacked with Draught of E'ci:<br>
850x3=2550+950=3500 dmg for 425+255 or 680 mana = 5.14 DPM<br>
or<br>
850x2=1700+950=2850 dmg for 680 mana = 4.19 DPM<br>
<br>
Ok so stacking a draught with a rain, even with one wave resisted (get malo) comes out to fractions below the damage per mana efficiency of strike of solusek alone.  If you get all 3 waves, the rains come out ahead by far.  And using rains stacked with smaller 1k sized nukes makes your aggro spread over time instead of being an almost 3000 point burst of aggro.<br>
<br>
I will remove the illiterate fucktard award I attempted to bestow in my above post and award one to myself for not addressing the true point and instead getting caught up in the 'OMG you said strike of solusek sucks' argument.<br>
