<br>
For SoS we get 25% mana save item (silk gloves, most rotting of all ele pieces).<br>
For SoS the ID items also have an effect.<br>
For rains we get innate 20% resist rate, regardless of debuffs on mobs.<br>
For rains the ID items do not have an effect.<br>
<br>
So... for SoS ele wizards get 30% (15% avg) ID item, 25% (12.5% avg) mana save and for rains we get 15% (7.5% avg) mana save and no ID.<br>
<br>
SoS is 2740x1.15 / 640x0.875 = 5.62 DPM<br>
ToM is 3x850x0.8 / 425x0.925 = 5.20 DPM<br>
ToM+DoE is 3x850x0.8 + 950x1.3 / 680x0.925 = 5.21<br>
<br>
As you can see, the rains/draughts efficiency isn't there for ele+ wizards. Furthermore with concussion and spell casting subtlety, the aggro isn't 3k big huge chunk and with SoS/Conc chain we bust out more dps, more dpm than with the rains/draughts you seem to favor. Next time you want to teach a wizard how to play their class, maybe you should think before opening your virtual mouth.<br>
